# n8n Node Help Text Standards

1. Info Boxes
   ```typescript
   // Essential information in yellow box
   {
     displayName: 'Notice',
     name: 'notice',
     type: 'notice',
     default: 'API rate limits apply: 100 requests per minute',
   },

   // Warning information
   {
     displayName: 'Warning',
     name: 'warning',
     type: 'notice',
     default: 'This operation cannot be undone',
     options: {
       variant: 'warning'
     }
   }
   ```

2. Parameter Hints
   ```typescript
   // Contextual information below field
   {
     displayName: 'Workspace ID',
     name: 'workspaceId',
     type: 'string',
     hint: 'Find this in your workspace settings',
   },

   // Hints with links
   {
     displayName: 'API Key',
     name: 'apiKey',
     type: 'string',
     hint: 'Get your API key from <a href="https://example.com/settings">account settings</a>',
   }
   ```

3. Node Hints
   ```typescript
   // Node level hints
   description: INodeTypeDescription = {
     displayName: 'My Node',
     name: 'myNode',
     hints: [
       {
         message: "Consider enabling <b>Execute Once</b> for better performance",
         type: 'info',
         location: 'outputPane',
         whenToDisplay: 'beforeExecution',
         displayCondition: '={{ $input.all().length > 1 }}'
       }
     ]
   };
   ```

4. Tooltips
   ```typescript
   // Field with tooltip
   {
     displayName: 'Update Method',
     name: 'updateMethod',
     type: 'options',
     description: 'Choose how to update existing records',
     options: [
       {
         name: 'Merge',
         value: 'merge',
         description: 'Only update specified fields',
       }
     ],
   }
   ```

5. Placeholder Text
   ```typescript
   // Input guidance
   {
     displayName: 'Email',
     name: 'email',
     type: 'string',
     placeholder: 'name@example.com',
   },

   // JSON example
   {
     displayName: 'Data',
     name: 'data',
     type: 'json',
     placeholder: '{\n  "name": "John",\n  "email": "john@example.com"\n}',
   }
   ```

6. Help Text Usage
   - Use info boxes sparingly for impact
   - Provide contextual parameter hints
   - Add tooltips only when helpful
   - Include clear placeholder text
   - Link to documentation when needed

7. Help Text Writing
   - Keep text concise and clear
   - Use consistent terminology
   - Provide examples where helpful
   - Link to additional resources
   - Update help text regularly

8. Dynamic Guidance
   - Adapt help based on context
   - Show relevant information
   - Hide irrelevant details
   - Provide progressive assistance
   - Handle all states properly

